Brandeis Math 232a: Code Examples
Unit 3: Quadrature
==========================
quadrat.py - Integrates a function using composite trapezoid and Simpson's
rules. Outputs the error as a function of the interval length h. 

Given data stored in the file "out", in Gnuplot the results can be shown with the command:

set logscale xy
plot 'out' u 2:3 t 'Trapezoidal' ps 2, 'out' u 2:4 t 'Simpson' ps 2

series_and_pade.nb - Mathematica notebook illustrating symbolic computations and Pade approximants

approx_driver.m - computes I(\epsilon) = \int_0^1 dx/(\epsilon+x^2) and compares \sqrt{\epsilon}I(\epsilon) to \pi/2
